caption.paragraph:
FIGURE 5.

Brachypeplus apicalis

, orig. A–E, G, I, K: specimens from QLD (“… Cape Tribulation, Pilgrim Sands…”); 
A
: body, dorsal; 
B
: head and thorax, ventral; 
C
: male anal sclerite and 
spiculum gastrale
, ventral; 
E
: tegmen, ventral; 
G
: penis trunk, dorsal; 
I
: proximal part of inner sac with armature; 
K
: ovipositor, ventral; D, F, H, J: specimen from Indonesian New Guinea (“Halmahera NW, 7 km N Jallolo….”); 
D
: male anal sclerite and 
spiculum gastrale
, ventral; 
F
: tegmen, ventral; 
H
: penis trunk, dorsal. Scale bars: 
a
= 1.0 mm to Fig. A; 
b
= 1.0 mm to Fig. B; 
с
= 0.25 mm to Figs C–K.
